AAXN Bexar County selects body camera coCommissioners also gave the Bexar County Sheriffs Office approval to negotiate a contract for body and dashboard cameras with Axon a company from Scottsdale Arizona The county has been trying to use bodyworn and incar dashboard cameras for years adding funding for cameras to the commissioners budget Sheriff Javier Salazar assured commissioners that accidental and purposeful video deletion would be very difficult to accomplish on Axon cameras Serrato said he did not have an estimate for how much the cameras would cost The contract the sheriffs office is pursuing with Axon would be for 550 cameras The sheriffs department also evaluated cameras from the Dallasbased company WatchGuard
